{"id":14880790,"mediaExerciseId":"dcc3be97-12e2-4ed4-847a-778bfeb8087e","exerciseName":"7","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":612274,"groupTitle":"Critical Thinking Questions","isPremium":true,"sectionName":null,"sectionTitle":null,"pageNumber":84,"solutions":[{"id":5908732,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we will learn about DuPont Identity.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":28,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/f4b071914b49f08ba4d412680b6a97e0/b859d16f30ae0bc20cdbae7a26e3cc2e/lateximg_large.png","width":709},"regular":{"height":15,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/f4b071914b49f08ba4d412680b6a97e0/b859d16f30ae0bc20cdbae7a26e3cc2e/lateximg.png","width":354}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define DuPont Identity.\n\n**DuPont Identity** is an expression that shows the Return on Equity (ROE) of a company.\n\nThe formula is denoted as follows:\n$$\\begin{aligned}\n\\textbf{ROE}& =\n \\text{Profit Margin} \\times\\text{Asset Turnover} \\times \\text{Financial Leverage}\\\\\\\\\n\\end{aligned}$$\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":200,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/f4b071914b49f08ba4d412680b6a97e0/b46bfd2083908f187c5bd6c2fadf9714/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":102,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/f4b071914b49f08ba4d412680b6a97e0/b46bfd2083908f187c5bd6c2fadf9714/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"The Du Pont Identity is a valuable tool for analyzing the performance of a firm because it emphasizes the firm's profitability, asset utilization efficiency, and financial leverage in determining the return on equity. \n\nDu Pont Identity ROE can also help develop future estimates of stock and dividend's growth rate. It also shows if the company's value is growing at an acceptable rate.\n","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":216,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/f4b071914b49f08ba4d412680b6a97e0/aca4191cd4f8fc92f84c21abdf3c5b20/lateximg_large.png","width":997},"regular":{"height":110,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/19/f4b071914b49f08ba4d412680b6a97e0/aca4191cd4f8fc92f84c21abdf3c5b20/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"e1e83ac0-4f01-434c-a5aa-1d597d43605b","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880791,"exerciseName":"8","page":84,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"f32234bd-ebf7-4a83-9fb6-8e9a090c7ae2","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-critical-thinking-questions-8-f32234bd-ebf7-4a83-9fb6-8e9a090c7ae2"},{"id":14880792,"exerciseName":"9","page":84,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"094cc003-698b-47c7-a193-e14be083e1ba","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-978125991